Microsoft Can Acquire Activision
--------------------------------

From the Wall Street Journal ( https://www.wsj.com/articles/microsoft-activ=
ision-blizzard-deal-ftc-hearing-d42675f1 ) :

Microsoft can close its $75 billion acquisition of Activision Blizzard, a f=
ederal judge ruled Tuesday, delivering a major setback to the Biden adminis=
tration=E2=80=99s attempt to rein in big mergers. The deal would combine Mi=
crosoft=E2=80=99s Xbox videogaming business with the publisher of popular f=
ranchises such as Call of Duty, World of Warcraft and Candy Crush. The ruli=
ng means there is no current U.S. obstacle to the two companies merging. Th=
e companies are still seeking U.K. merger approval and it wasn=E2=80=99t im=
mediately clear whether the holdup there would delay closing. The bid, howe=
ver, got a boost Tuesday when Britain=E2=80=99s Competition and Markets Aut=
hority said it was prepared to consider new proposals from Microsoft for ad=
dressing its competition concerns.

U.S. District Judge Jacqueline Scott Corley said in her opinion that the Fe=
deral Trade Commission hadn=E2=80=99t shown that Microsoft=E2=80=99s owners=
hip of Activision games would hurt competition in the console or cloud-gami=
ng markets. =E2=80=9CTo the contrary, the record evidence points to more co=
nsumer access to Call of Duty and other Activision content,=E2=80=9D she wr=
